{"id": 237074714, "title": "\u2018Postcard Bandit\u2019 sues WA government for wrongful imprisonment", "text": "He claims the imposition of a sentence without the intervention of a court \u201coffends\u201d the strict separation of the judiciary and legislative arms of government at federal level. His lawyers say that the case may ultimately need to be determined by the High Court. Counsel for Abbott, Matthew Crowley, said the real question was \u201cnot whether we like Mr Abbott or not\u201d. \u201cViews will differ about that, just like they did about Ned Kelly 150 years ago,\u201d he said. \u201cThe real question is the constitutional power the state has to keep people in prison after their sentences end \u2013 without trial, verdict, or sentence \u2013 even if they don\u2019t like them.\u201d", "summary": "He will challenge the constitutional validity of laws which require an inmate returned to prison after an escape to serve an additional period of imprisonment equal to one-third of the time they were at large, on top of the time they had yet to serve.", "url": "https://www.smh.com.au/national/western-australia/postcard-bandit-sues-wa-government-for-wrongful-imprisonment-20240618-p5jmn7.html", "image": "https://static.ffx.io/images/$zoom_1.4537%2C$multiply_0.7554%2C$ratio_1.777778%2C$width_1059%2C$x_0%2C$y_183/t_crop_custom/q_86%2Cf_auto/59ba6163a7a3e1916d67ccc04c0e9a6685d807f7", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-18 00:07:32", "author": "Abe Maddison", "authors": ["Abe Maddison"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "au", "sentiment": -0.219}